President Obama to Travel to Columbus, Ohio





	WASHINGTON â€“ On Tuesday, September 13, the President will travel to Columbus, Ohio, to talk about the bipartisan proposals to grow the economy and create jobs as part of the American Jobs Act that he will unveil in his speech to a joint session of Congress tonight.
